(Grad Cafe data is useful for learning SQL because it contains many real-looking application) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(records, but it is not a representative sample of all graduate school applicants. The site) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(depends on anonymous self-submission, so the data can overrepresent people who are) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(especially motivated to report good news, bad news, or unusual outcomes. It can also contain) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(missing values, inconsistent labels, duplicate-looking entries, rounding, exaggeration, or) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(mistakes because there is no admissions office verifying each GPA, GRE score, school name,) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(program, or decision status. Those limits mean the SQL answers should be read as patterns in) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(the submitted Grad Cafe records, not as official statistics about graduate admissions.) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
() Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(The analysis results may look surprising when compared with national or institutional) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(standards because the people who report to Grad Cafe are probably not distributed like the) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(full applicant population. For example, an average GRE quantitative score from Grad Cafe can) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(be much higher than a broader benchmark if applicants with strong scores are more willing to) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(disclose them, if international STEM applicants are overrepresented, or if users without) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(scores leave the field blank and are excluded from averages. Similar selection effects can) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(affect acceptance rates, GPA averages, and school-specific counts. The data is still) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(valuable for exploratory analysis, but the limitations make careful wording important: the) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 11 Tf
(results describe anonymous self-reported entries, not verified admissions outcomes.) Tj
